14. All documents needed to operate the UAS and conduct its operations in accordance
with the conditions and limitations stated in this grant of exemption, are hereinafter
referred to as the operating documents. At a minimum, the operating documents must
include:
a. Elementary Watson’s operations manual;
b. Elementary Watson’s training program;
c. The manufacturer’s provided flight manual;
d. All other manufacturer UAS provided documents;
e. This exemption; and
f. Any ATO-issued COA that applies to operations under this exemption.
These operating documents must be accessible during all UAS operations that occur
under this exemption and made available to the Administrator or any law enforcement
official upon request. If a discrepancy exists between the conditions and limitations in
this exemption and the procedures outlined in the operating documents, the
conditions and limitations herein take precedence and must be followed. Otherwise,
Elementary Watson must follow the procedures as outlined in its operating
documents.
15. Elementary Watson must have and keep current a comprehensive operations Manual
that is tailored for their proposed operation and contain, at a minimum:
a. Operations policies, methods, and procedures that address Safety Risk
Management (SRM);
b. Adverse weather;
c. Flight planning;
d. NOTAM;
e. Aircraft inspection;
f. Preflight duties and post-flight duties;
g. Normal and emergency flight procedures;
h. Crew Resource Management (CRM) and communications,
i. Crewmember responsibilities (to include operations with and without a VO);
j. Accident reporting;
k. Hazardous material (HAZMAT) handling and stowage; and
l. UAS maintenance;
m. Operation at Night (if operating at night);
n. Multi-UAS Operation (if operating multi-UAS);
o. Multi-UAS Operation at Night (if operating multi-UAS at Night); and
p. Operation without a VO (if operating without a VO).
